The participants' average age was 20.98, and 89.5% of them were women. In addition, 32.6% were seniors and 27.0% were juniors. Only 36.8% replied that they had been provided with information about MERS-CoV, and 76.5% mentioned “Remedies for MERS-CoV” as information that they wanted to have about the virus (Table 2
). There was a significant difference in preventive behavior according to gender and grade among general characteristics (p
 < .01; Table 2).
